CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, October 24, 1959, pg. 3 reads: "Where Mother Visited - Denying that she was "out of town" Mrs. Dupree said she had left her home (arrow one) to give flour to a neighbor in an adjacent house (arrow two) and pie to her mother in a house across the street (arrow three). "I was gone only about 20 minutes," she said, in telling about the fire tragedy."Image published in Pittsburgh Courier with graphic addition of arrow.
TitMainTitle: Row houses along Washington Street, Braddock
